laboratory_examinations.findings: Liver demonstrates diffusely decreased attenuation, possibly reflecting hepatic steatosis. Multiple pulmonary nodules present, measuring 6.6 mm, 6.2 mm, and 8.4 mm, new since prior study. Diverticulosis with wall thickening and adjacent fat stranding in the sigmoid colon.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: New pulmonary nodules compared to prior study.
